    "monuments-blog-info-nine-1" -> Array(
      "JUMA MOSQUE\nAccording to later research, the Juma Mosque in Khazarasp is one of the oldest mosques in Central Asia. Archaeologists from the Khorezm Mamun Academy have unearthed a tomb, which was founded in the 10th century.\n   The mosque, which now has only one wall and one wooden carved door, was once a multi-columned mosque (5 rows) like the Juma Mosque in Khiva. The total size is 25x21 m. Today, the pillars and some marble slabs have been preserved. The walls of the mosque are decorated with shallow arched shelves and no other decorations. The altar remains on the south wall. The door of the mosque is decorated with wonderful examples of wooden carvings - Islamic patterns. The pillars and doors of the mosque, the roofs were looted during the Soviet era. Due to the fact that the walls of the mosque are open, cracks have appeared due to the rain, and the mosque needs urgent repair and restoration. If the mosque is closed in the old way, it can be used here to organize a museum and develop tourism.\n                                                    JUMA MOSQUE\n   The mosque is the house of Allah, the building for prayer. Khiva's Jumaʼ (Juma) mosque was one of the city's most prominent buildings in the Middle Ages, with its unique construction and size. The mosque is 55x46m in area and has many columns. The building is located on the main street that connects the eastern and western gates of Ichon Fortress.\n   Al-Maqdisi, an Arab traveler who came to Khorezm in the 10th century, first mentioned the Juma Mosque in Khiva. The old mosque was demolished and replaced in 1788 by the same plan. The exterior of the mosque is very simple, with a height of 4.5 meters and a height of 42 meters. The gate of the mosque was built to the north, and the wind from the north came out of two large holes in the middle of the mosque. At the foot of the tunnel, in ancient times, grew mulberry trees, which helped to clean the air inside the mosque. The Juma Mosque is a one-story flat-roofed building with a suspended ceiling of 213 columns measuring 3.15 x 3.15 meters.\n   The altar of the mosque is located on the south wall of the room. The altar has high shelves on the sides and a high ceiling to make it stand out as usual. The simple plaster ornaments on the dome of the altar and the colorful openings on the wall near the ornament depicting lilies and namataks were made in the late 18th and 20th centuries. The marble stones on both sides of the altar are engraved with carved letters, one of which is a waqf dated 1203 AH (1788-89) on the occasion of the donation of the mosque's property and funds. It states that in 1203 AH, by order of Minister Abdurahman, foundations were allotted to the mosque in the villages of Kuyuktom (now Goktom, a village in the Koshkopir district) and Bekabad, and the proceeds were donated to charity and mosque needs. The second marble slab is slightly smaller and has a date of 1080 AH (1666).\n  The inscription on the carved door on the southern facade states that the mosque was renovated in 1788-89 under the leadership of Abdurahman Mehtar. Inside the mosque, 15 of the ancient carved pillars have been preserved. The oldest pillars have flattened petals, the upper part of the body has a regular ridge, and in the middle there is a Kufic inscription with a circular pattern, and the shapes are deeply engraved. The columns of the 14th century are rich in patterns and inscriptions.\n  This rare monument was restored in 1979-1983 and 1996-1997. It currently serves as an architectural object for tourists.\n\n               YORMUHAMMAD DEVON (SAYYID OTA) MOSQUE\n  The Yormuhammad Devon Mosque is also known as the Sayyid Ata Mosque because it is located next to the mausoleum of Sayyid Alovuddin and is named in memory of this great man. The mosque is connected to the Abdurasulboy madrasah on the east side.\n   Munis and Ogahi's Firdavs ul Iqbal gives a lot of information about the activities of Yor Muhammad's devonbegi, including the saying that \"the mahrami asrori sahibkirani (the closest person who shares the khan's secrets) is Yormuhammad devonbegi.\" Devonbegi was from the house of Sayyids, and the inscriptions on the altar of the mosque tell about it: \"The builder of the mosque is still a descendant of the blessed governor Muhammad ...\".\n  The mosque was built for a smaller mahalla at the time, and for many years, residents of the mahalla performed Friday prayers.\n\n                                       TOSHMASJID MOSQUE\n   Toshmasjid is a mahalla mosque built in the late 18th century. The building was built in the architectural tradition of this period. Archaeologists who have studied the tomb have found that it was used as a public venue even before it was built. Indeed, to this day, the Toshmasjid holds mass ceremonies and events.\n   Over time, the building has been refurbished and renovated for various uses. In 1997, on the occasion of the 2500th anniversary of Khiva, the building was completely renovated and restored to its original state on the basis of a scientifically developed project.\n   With the aim of rational use of the building, it was transferred to Soyot mahalla, taking into account the request and initiative of community activists.\n                                    HASAN MUROD KUSHBEGI MOSQUE\n   Hasan Murad Kushbegi Mosque was built in the late 18th and early 19th centuries near the Garden Gate. The mosque was built by the brothers Hasan Murad and Niyaz.\n  The mosque has a winter mosque covered with a single-column summer porch and dome. The mosque is not much different from the residential buildings. The doors are decorated with Islamic patterns.\n  The main minaret of the Hasan Murad Kushbegi mosque has not been preserved. At present, only a small tower to the left of the entrance door in the façade section has been preserved.\n  At present, the mosque has a wood carving workshop.\n\n                              BAGHBONLI MOSQUE (GARDEN MOSQUE)\n   The Baghbonli Mosque is located southeast of the Ichan Qala. This mahalla mosque was built in 1809 by Pahlavon Kuli and is famous for its beauty.\n   The mosque was replaced by the Zubaydakhanim mosque, which was originally built of raw brick in the style of nigirik (chubkori). More than two hundred years after the mosque was rebuilt, locals consider the tomb attached to it to the west to be the \"Queen's Tomb.\" This tomb is the tomb of Zubaydahanim.\n  The mosque with a large dome is reminiscent of a monument of the XIV-XV centuries, due to its interior decoration, the carvings of the two pillars of the porch, and the hadiths written on them.\n   The inscription on the marble plaque on the wall above the entrance to the mosque is in Persian, Nasta'liq script, and its translation is as follows:\nGood quality master Pahlavonquli,\nHe received help from the grace of Allah.\nFor the honesty of his wife,\nFor the sake of the Almighty.\nHe built a magnificent high mosque,\nShe received her beauty and purity from heaven.\nEmbroidered like an ornate gold coin,\nAll the domes and ceilings delight the tongue.\nBuild his heart palace and religion,\nFree your body from the fire of hell.\nOne thousand two hundred and twenty-four,\nIt’s a wonderful history, O vigilant one.\n                      ATAMUROD (MATRIZO) KUSHBEGI MOSQUE\n   Otamurod (Matrizo) Kushbegi Mosque was built in 1816 by Otamurod Kushbegi as a mahalla mosque in Ichan Qala. The date 1232 AH is preserved on a marble pillar on the summer porch of the mosque. The minaret of the mosque has not been preserved. The mosque also has a multi-column summer awning and a winter mosque built in the shape of a square.\n   The Atamurod Kushbegi Mosque has a summer terrace with an altar on the qibla side, a pulpit for sermons on the right side of the altar, and an entrance to the winter mosque on the left side and special places for reciting the Qur'an. The altar is arched and the stalactites are decorated with ganch.\n  The summer porch of the mosque is notable for its carved columns. The 6 pillars of the summer terrace consist of 4 arches and 2 steps in terms of construction techniques and are perfectly designed in an architectural composition.\n  Baked bricks measuring 26.0 x 26.0 x 4.5 cm were used in the construction of the mosque. There is a toilet in the north-eastern part of the mosque.\n\n                                              OQMASJID MOSQUE\n  The exterior of the mosque, a cool shady porch surrounded on three sides, and the three doors of the domed building indicate that the mosque is a public meeting place. Its ancient part (foundation) was built at the same time as the Anushakhan bath. However, the inscriptions on the carved doors indicate that the building was built in 1838-1842. By the same time, all the buildings around the square were largely built, and now the masters had to build on the remaining small stage. The architecture of this building was supposed to reflect the majesty of the square, to be indistinguishable from the neighboring residential buildings, and the masters of Khiva performed this task perfectly.\n   The dome of the mosque consists of a room and a porch, and the central dome is set in a room (6.35 x 6.35). The room was expanded using porches. The structure of the porch and the side walls clearly define the facade composition of the mosque. The dome, which rises high above the flat roof, together with the square base, gives a distant staircase. The convenient location of the mosque allowed the altar to be placed on the south wall. This allows you to pray equally in the room and on the porch. When the masters built and decorated the mosque, they built it in a simple style and limited themselves to giving simple decorations. There are almost no carvings on the wooden pillars, only the top of the pillar is made of arbitrary plates. The Islamic patterns and silence of the doors are designed in the same style.\n  At present, the mosque has a handicraft workshop.\n\n                                SHAYKH KABIR MOSQUE\n  The Sheikh Kabir Mosque was built in the cemetery area around the Pahlavon Mahmud Mausoleum, in the northern part of the complex. Sheikh Kabir Mosque was built during the reign of Muhammad Rahimkhan II.\n  The three-dimensional composition of the Sheikh Kabir Mosque is north-south, with a large dome in the mosque. The layout of the mosque is simple, with a wooden carved door, a large dome, muqarnas in the corners of the dome, and a separate porch of the mosque. The altar and shelves on the qibla wall of the porch, as well as the beautiful wooden pillars and pillars on the porch add a special charm to the mosque.\n According to the plan of the Sheikh Kabir Mosque, the total dimensions are 10.20 x 10.0 meters, and the height of the roof of the mosque is 4.50 meters. The height of the dome of the mosque is 11.55 meters.\nToday, the Sheikh Kabir Mosque is beautifully renovated\n\n                                                     TOWERS\n                                     JUMA MOSQUE TOWER\n   The minaret of the Juma Mosque is located on the side of a large street that connects the two gates of the Ichan Qala, the eastern-Polvon and the western-Ota gates, and represents the mosque for Friday prayers. The tower is made of baked bricks in the form of a cone and is decorated with green tiles in the form of rings in seven parts of the body. The upper part is made of embossed bricks. In 1996-1997, the Juma Mosque was renovated. In terms of tower height, it is the second largest in Khiva after the Islamic Khoja Tower. The diameter of the base is 6.2 m and the height is 32.5 m.\n   According to researcher Abdulla Abdurasulov, there is a legend about the construction of the minaret of the Juma mosque: there is a cauldron in the middle of the mosque, the word of which was kept cold in the summer. The worshipers were thirsty in the heat, drank cold water and gave alms. The imam of the mosque divided the money into three parts and collected one part, the other two parts were used for the expenses of the mosque and charity for the widows. After a certain period of time, the imam gave the collected money to the masters and rebuilt the minaret for the mosque in such a way that it would not be less or more than this amount. The masters used the donated money for the tower and built a beautiful monument.\n  When the construction of the minaret was completed, the imam thanked God and said to the worshipers: He said that he would spend the money on useless things.\n\n                                           ABDOL BOBO TOWER\n   Abdol bobo tower was built in the complex of the same name, in the eastern part of Deshon Qala, at the junction of Polvon gate and Khazarasp (Sheep) gates. Deshon is located on K.Otaev Street. This minaret is a minaret of the mosque, built after the death of Pahlavon Ahmad Zamchi (original name of Abdol Baba). There are stairs leading up to the inside. Despite the compactness of the tower, which gives the complex awe, it looks very scary, and the height of the yoghurt becomes sharply thinner. The tower is given a special cork by the quiet honor at the top of it. The tower is now renovated.\n   There are different opinions about Abdol bobo or Pahlavon Ahmad Zamchi was the commander of the Khorasan army during the reign of Abu Muslim. He lived in Marv, the capital of Khorasan, until the end of his life. His tomb was in the city of Marv, during the reign of Allakulikhan (1825-1842) the khaki was brought and a mausoleum, a pool and a mosque were built. Abdol bobo means the eldest of the chiltons (sheikh murids).\n   According to other sources, after the assassination of Caliph Jafar, Abu Muslim fled from the caliph's spies, came to Khorezm and died in Khiva.\n   According to some sources, the tower is associated with the name of Ahmad Zamchi (XII century), the commander of Khorezmshah Atsiz.\n  \n\n                                     SAYYID SHOLIKORBOY TOWER\n   The Sayyid Sholikorboy tower, built in 1835, stands out in the Deshon Qala of Khiva. It is located in the courtyard of the mosque of the same name on Polvon Qori Street. The tower is made of baked bricks in the form of a vertical cone, the height is 24 meters, the diameter of the base is 4.5 meters. The tower narrows from the bottom to the top. The narrowing of the tower made it stronger. The top of the tower is reached by 62 stairs. The top of the tower is finished with a glass hole and very skillfully designed rafters. The mezana is decorated under the cornice in honor of the top. At the top of the tower there are 4 large arches, built to the west.\n   It is noteworthy that no tiles were used at all from the bottom to the top of the tower. Our great architects skillfully decorated the bricks with great skill in the construction of the tower. However, today the tower is tilted 1.07 meters to the south-west. This is due to the rise of groundwater in the area (70 cm - 1 meter below ground level), the failure of traffic and drainage systems. At present, the researchers of the Khorezm Mamun Academy are Ph.D. Under the scientific guidance of G. Durdiyeva, they are conducting research on the restoration of the Sayyid Sholikorboy tower. Even today, Khiva residents use the Sayyid Sholikorboy complex for Friday prayers.\n   There is a rumor among the people that only one master worked on the construction of this mosque. Each child was given one nut for each brick they brought. Every day, children rushed to the mosque to get more nuts. A mosque was built and worshipers began to pray. On the day of Eid, the khan went to the mosque outside the Ichan Qala to perform the Eid prayer with his relatives. Sayyid Niyaz wondered, \"Why did the khan say that?\" He then began construction of a madrassa on the east side of the mosque so that the khan's words would not remain in the air. \" There are three doors on three sides of the mosque and the entrance to the mosque is through a porch from the main entrance on the north side. There are three columns on the porch. They reflect the best traditions of wood carving. The walls of the porch are decorated with figured panels.\n\n                                     MUHAMMAD AMINKHAN TOWER\n   One of the architectural monuments in Khiva is the Muhammad Aminkhan Tower, located in front of the main complex of the unfinished Muhammad Aminkhan Madrasah. In 1853, on the orders of Khiva khan Muhammad Aminkhan, the construction of a tower began at the foot of the Old Ark in the western part of the Ichan Qala. Currently, the street where the tower is located is called Polvon Qori Street.\n    According to the Khiva historian Munis, in 1855 Muhammad Aminkhan marched into northern Iran and was captured and executed by the Turkmen in Sarakhs with 20 captains. Therefore, the tower was left unfinished until the end.\n   When completed, the tower was planned to be 70-80 meters high, which could be the tallest and most beautiful tower in Central Asia. The current height of the tower is 26 meters, the base circumference is 14.2 meters and has a truncated cone shape. The tower is still magnificent and beautiful. The tower is dominated by geometric patterns and is completely covered with tiles. The tiles are designed in blue, green, nile and white, which are called \"cold backgrounds\" in architecture. Although the tower was built more than 1.5 centuries ago, its color has not changed. It is known that the sun's rays on the tower change the color of its tiles. However, the color of the tiles of the tower has not changed. Access to the tower is by stairs. The stairs are being repaired. At the top of the tower is a 12-line poem by Ogahi, written on tiles and erased in the 1920s. In 1997, on the occasion of the 2,500th anniversary of the city of Khiva, a 12-line poem by Ogahi was revived by master repairman Rustam Tokhirov. Ogahi wrote the year it was built. The infinite celestial column was built in 1268 AH and 1852 AD.\n    At the beginning of the XX century, our people called it \"ulli minor\", \"blue minor\", and today - \"short minor\". Poets and nobles described the tower as a \"pillar on the porch of the sky\" after the end of poetic history.\n   The Muhammad Aminkhan Madrasa was converted into a hotel in 1979 and still serves tourists.\n\n                                      FOUR SHABBOZ TOWER\n   The Four Shabboz Tower was built in 1885 at the entrance to the complex of the same name near the intersection of R. Ollaberganov and Four Shavvoz streets. Shabboz or shavvoz is actually shahboz, and the word shahboz means greatness. The diameter of the foundation is 3.5 meters, height - 12 meters, and rises from a special place through a bypass. The body is decorated with blue ribbons, the upper part is decorated with blue glazed tiles. The tower was renovated in 1996.\n  The Four Shabboz Bobo complex is located in the Mevaston neighborhood of Deshon Qala in the northwestern part of Khiva. The complex includes a swimming pool, a minaret, a mosque and a madrasa, as well as a cemetery and a number of tombs. The complex was once called the Tomb of the Four Kingdoms. Below we list their names. Saint Qutbil - Hasanquli Azizon, Qazi Muhammad Azizon, John Muhammad Azizon, Isfandiyarkhan ibn Arab Muhammadkhan. Isfandiyarkhan was a wise and just king. He was buried in the cemetery in Khiva's Mevaston neighborhood. Now it is called Tort Shahboz. The rectangular marble on     Isfandiyarkhan's tomb is decorated with beautiful plant motifs and inscriptions in Arabic and Persian in the style of Suls script. The words \"Nur Muhammad Sultan Isfandiyarkhan\" are written on one side of the tombstone, and the date of his death in Arabic on the other side. The tomb, which is written in Persian on the other two sides, is now on display at the Museum of the History of the Khiva Khanate at the Muhammad Rahimkhan Madrasa.\n   Gradually, the complex expanded, with a 12-meter-high tower built in the 17th century, and the tower and other structures renovated in the mid-19th century and in 1996. According to the inscription on the door of the mosque of the Four Shavvoz complex (read by E. Rtveladze), the mosque was built in 1875 by a master (or customer) named Muhammad Nazarbay.\n\n                                  TORA MUROD TORA TOWER\n   Also known as Amir Tora Tower. In the Khiva khanate the princes, ie the sons of the khans, were called tora. Tora Murod Tora Tower was built in 1888 by Tora Murod Tora, the brother of Muhammad Rahimkhan II, under the mahalla mosque of the same name.\n  The minaret was built in front of the mahalla mosque in front of the north-western corner of Muhammad Rahimkhan II - Feruz madrasah. The tower is made of ornate brick and decorated with blue bows. The upper background is arched, finished with two rows of bricks. Dimensions: diameter of the foundation - 3.2 meters, height about 9 meters.\n\n                                       SHAYKH MAVLON BOBO TOWER\n   The tower of Sheikh Mavlon Baba is located in the village of Eski Qiyot in the cemetery of the same name. It was built in the XIX century under the mosque of Sheikh Mavlon Bobo. The mosque and minaret were renovated in 1999 to mark the 190th anniversary of the birth of Muhammad Reza Ogahi. The height of the tower is 11 meters.\n   In the cemetery of Sheikh Mavlon Bobo there is a grave of Shermuhammad Munis and Muhammad Riza Erniyozbek oglu Ogahi. The mausoleum was renovated in 1989-1999 and has an area of \u200B\u200B120 m2.\n   Sheikh Mavlon Baba Complex is connected with the name of Sheikh Mavlon, a religious leader who lived in the XVII century. The complex consists of a mausoleum, a khanaqah, a porch, a courtyard, a mosque and a minaret.\n\n                    BIKAJON BIKA (SHOKALANDAR BOBO) TOWER\n   Among the towers is the Bikajon Bika tower, located in the Deshon Qala of Khiva, north of the Ota gate. The minaret was built during the reign of Khiva khan Muhammad Rahimkhan II - Feruz (1864-1910), ie in 1894 at the initiative of the khan's sister Bikajon Bika between the mosque and madrasah of the same name. The reason why the tower differs from other towers is that Bikajon Bika tower is the only tower built by a woman in Central Asia. Bikajon Bika built the tower in honor of her husband Shokalandarbobo, which is why the tower is also called Shokalandarbobo tower. Bikajon Bika dedicated the tower to her husband because they had no children. This tower stands as a monument to them. According to the elders, the tower was built by the village master.\n   According to sources, Rahnatullo Yasovulboshi initially used a marble foundation to build a madrasah in the area where the Bikajon Bika complex was built, but the construction work was stopped for 4 years. The tower is made of baked bricks in the form of a cone, 20 meters high, the base circumference is 6 meters. Inside the summer mosque, there is a corridor to the top through a spiral staircase through a special door. At the top of the tower there are four-sided arches.\n   The tower was built at the intersection of Polvon Qori and Kalandarov streets, near the Hospitality Square. The tower is currently under repair.\n\n                                             SAINT CHILLA TOWER\n   The  Saint Chilla  or Chilla Saint Tower was built in the 19th century near the mosque of the same name. It is located at the intersection of K. Yakubov Street in the fortress. It is derived from the name of the forty saints. The height of the tower is 17 meters and is made of baked bricks. From the bottom to the top through the roundabout to the top. The upper part of the tower is decorated with bow tiles. The top of the lantern has a dome, the body is made of white and blue tiles. The mosque has not been preserved and the minaret has been repaired.\n\n                                     PIGEON HOUSE TOWER\n   The dovecote tower is the minaret of the neighborhood mosque of the same name. The dovecote is a specially built structure for storing pigeons, which was discovered during archeological excavations. Pigeon tower is derived from the name of the same people and mosque. It can be assumed that in ancient times there was a pigeon house in this area. In 2009-2011, scientists of the Khorezm Mamun Academy, under the leadership of archaeologist Sh. Matrasulov, identified the location of the pigeon house 5-7 km southwest of Khiva. This pigeon house is part of a settlement called Axunlar, which dates back to the XII-XIII centuries. We assume that the dovecote at Akhunlar was destroyed during the Mongol invasion, and the present dovecote mahalla was formed.\n   The tower is made of baked bricks and has a corridor to the top through a special door. At the top there are four arches. The diameter of the tower is 3.2 meters and the height is 9 meters.\n\n                                      SHOHIMARDON BOBO TOWER\n   Shohimardon Bobo Tower was built in the XIX century in Pahlavon Mahmud mahalla between Shohimardon mosque and madrasah. Up to 5 meters high, the tile is decorated with bows. The tower has been repaired.\n  There is no information about the tower in the literature.\n\n                          MAMAT (MUHAMMAD) MAHRAM TOWER\n   Muhammad Mahram Tower was built in 1903 in the complex of the same name. The minaret is located in the south-western corner of the madrasah at the intersection of A. Boltaev and Anash Khalfa streets. The main diameter of the tower is 4.2 meters, height is 20 meters. The upper part of the tower is delicately finished with glazed tiles. The tower is decorated with white and purple tiles. At the top of the tower there is a copper dome.\n\n                                              POLVON QORI TOWER\n   Polvon Qori Tower was built in 1905 in a compact and new style of baked brick near the mosque and the minaret of the same name. The tower is located at the intersection of Polvon Qori and M. Qoriyev streets. It was built by the great Khiva merchant Polvon Qori. The foundation of the tower is covered with 25 cm thick marble. Its construction technique and style are reminiscent of the Kalon Minaret in Bukhara.\n   The bricks are made in the terracotta style. The upper part of the tower is made of carved bricks and decorated with green tiles and bows. The height is 30 meters, the base is cylindrical. The Polvon Qori Tower is the most monumental structure in the Deshon Qala, is inextricably linked with the long chain of Ichan Qala towers running from east to west.\n    \n\n                             ISLAM KHOJA TOWER (ULLIMINOR)\n   Today, the Islamic Haji Tower, along with the mausoleum of Pahlavon Mahmud, has become a symbol of the city of Khiva. It was built in the traditional style by Islam Khoja in 1908-1910 under the madrasa of the same name. The Tower is located in the southern part of the qala and can be seen from around the city. It is the tallest monument in Khorezm. Although the tower was built in the ancient style, the influence of Russian-European architecture of that time is noticeable. The upper part is very slender, and the top is finished with a beautiful cornice and a domed lantern. The top of the tower is covered with green, blue, laurel and white vinegar bricks. That is why the upper part of the tower stands out. The ornate frames of the vinegar turn the conical body of the tower into a circular circle in several places. With this in mind, the elders say, \"The Lord's Tower has four seasons and twelve months' decoration.\"\n   The tower was built by master Khudoiberdi khoja. Bolta Vaisov and Madaminov, masters from the village of Madir in Khanka, took part in the decoration of the tower on the basis of patterns designed by Eshmuhammad Khudaiberdiev.\n  In the simple and clear form and decoration of the tower, a new picture 24 enters the architecture of Khiva. Islamic Hodja Tower. style structures can be seen. The peculiarities of Khiva's architecture of that period were reflected in the construction of new types of buildings - post office, telegraph, new style Jadid school and hospital.\n  In addition to the ancient methods of construction and decoration, the masters used Russian bricklaying, new-shaped arches and roofs in the construction of these buildings. In connection with the construction of the tower, the poet Niazi completed a 48-line poetic history, which was engraved on the marble by the master Khudaibergan Muhrkan and placed ten meters above the ground. The 2.5-meter dome at the top of the tower is made of a metal called patal (a mixture of bronze, brass and copper). This metal dome shone like gold for a while. The dome of the tower was renovated on the eve of the 2,500th anniversary of the city of Khiva and covered with a layer of gold.\n  The Islam Khoja Tower is one of the largest and most beautiful monuments in Central Asia due to its beauty, structure and height.",
      "МЕЧЕТЬ ЖУМА\nСогласно последующим исследованиям, Джума-мечеть в Хазараспе является одной из старейших мечетей в Центральной Азии. Археологи из Хорезмской академии Мамуна в ходе раскопок обнаружили, что мечеть была основана в 10 веке.\nМечеть, у которой сейчас остались только стены и единственная резная деревянная дверь, в свое время была многоколонной (5-рядной) мечетью, как и Джума-мечеть в Хиве. Общий объём 25х21 м. Сейчас сохранились столбы и несколько мраморных плит. Стены мечети украшены неглубокими полками в виде арок, других украшений нет. На южной стене сохранилось расположение алтаря. Двери мечети украшены прекрасными образцами резьбы по дереву - исламскими узорами. Столбы и двери мечети, крыша были разграблены еще в советское время. В связи с тем, что стены мечети находятся в открытом состоянии, под воздействием дождя образовались трещины, и мечеть требует срочного ремонта и реставрационных работ. Если мечеть закроют по старинке, ее можно использовать для организации музея и развития туризма.\n\n\n\nМЕЧЕТЬ ДЖУМА\nМечеть – это дом Аллаха, здание для молитвы. Мечеть Джомеъ (Джума) Хивы была одной из самых выдающихся построек города в средние века, отличалась уникальной конструкцией и размерами. Мечеть занимает площадь 55х46 м и построена с множествами колонн. Это здание расположено на стороне главной улицы, соединяющей восточные и западные ворота Ичанкала.\nАль-Макдиси, арабский путешественник, приехавший в Хорезм в X веке, впервые упомянул мечеть Джума в Хиве. Старая мечеть была снесена и заменена в более широкую настоящую мечеть в 1788 году по тому же плану. Внешний вид здания мечети очень простой, высота 4,5 метра, высота минарета 42 метра. Ворота мечети были построены с видом на север, и ветер, дующий с севера, выходил из двух больших отверстий, открытых в центре мечети. Под отверстиями в старину росли тутовые деревья, которые помогали очищать воздух внутри мечети в этот период. Джума-мечеть представляет собой одноэтажное здание с плоской крышей с 213 столбами размером 3,15x3,15 метра.\nАлтарь мечети расположен на южной стене помещения. У алтаря по бокам высокие полки, чтобы он, как обычно, выделялся, а потолок приподнят. Простые гипсовые орнаменты на куполе алтаря и красочные проемы в стене возле орнамента с изображением лилий и нектаринов выполнены в конце XVIII - XX вв. На мраморных камнях с обеих сторон алтаря выгравированы резные письма, одна из которых - вакф, датированный 1203 г. хиджры (1788-89 гг.) по случаю пожертвования имущества и средств мечети. В нем говорится, что по приказу визира Абдурахмана в 1203 году хиджры в деревнях Куюктом (Гуктом - теперь деревня в Кушкупырском районе) и Бекабаде были выделены земли для фонда мечети, а вырученные средства были использованы на благотворительность и нужды мечети. Вторая мраморная плита немного меньше, на ней написана дата 1080 хиджры (1666 г.)\nНадпись на резной двери южного фасада гласит, что мечеть была отремонтирована в 1788-89 годах под руководством личности Абдурахмона Мехтара. Внутри мечети сохранилось 15 старинных резных столбов. Самые старые столбы имеют приплюснутые листья, верхняя часть тулова равномерно зачесана, а посередине - куфическая надпись, формы глубоко выгравированы. В колоннах XIV века много узоров, а надписи даны в письмах насх.\nЭтот редкий памятник реставрировали в 1979–1983 и 1996–1997 годах. В настоящее время служит для туристов как архитектурный объект.\n\n\n\nМЕЧЕТЬ ЁРМУХАММАДА ДЕВОНА (САЙЙИД ОТА)\nМечеть Ёрмухаммада Девона также называют мечетью Саййид ота, причина этому, мечеть расположена недалеко от мавзолея Саййида Аловуддина и названа в память об этом великом человеке. Мечеть соединена с медресе Абдурасулбая с восточной стороны\nВ произведении “Фирдавс ул икбол» Муниса и Огахи даются много информации о деятельности девонбеги Ёр Мухаммада, в частности говорится так: «махрами асрори сахибкирани (ближайший к хану человек, с которым делит свои секреты) Ёрмухаммад девонбеги». Девонбеги был из родов сайидов, об этом свидетельствуют надписи, сохранившиеся на алтаре мечети: Масжидки бинокард хамон бахш валият авлоди Мухаммад...”\nВ то время мечеть была построена для небольшого квартала, и многие годы жители мечети совершали пятничные молитвы.\n\n\nТОШ (КАМЕННАЯ) МЕЧЕТЬ\nТош (каменная) мечеть – это махаллинская мечеть, построенная в конце ХVIII века. Здание построено в архитектурных традициях того периода. Археологи, изучавшие Тошмечеть, обнаружили, что еще до того, как она была построена, это было место, где люди проводили массовые мероприятия. Действительно, и по сей день в Тошмечете проводятся массовые церемонии и мероприятия.\nЗдание было отремонтировано и обновлено с течением времени, чтобы использовать его для различных целей. В 1997 году по случаю 2500-летнего юбилея Хивы здание было полностью отремонтировано и восстановлено до первоначального состояния на основе научно разработанного проекта.\nВ целях рационального использования здания, с учетом просьбы и инициативы общественных активистов, оно было передано Соётской махалле для сохранения.\n\n\n\nМЕЧЕТЬ ХАСАНА МУРОДАКУШБЕГИ\nМечеть Хасана Мурада Кушбеги была построена в конце XVIII - начале XIX веков недалеко от ворот Богча. Данную мечеть построили братья Хасан Мурад кушбеги вместе с Нияз оталик.\nМечеть имеет зимнюю мечеть, перекрытую одноколонным летним крыльцом и куполом. Мечеть мало чем отличается от жилых домов. Двери украшены исламскими узорами.\nГлавный минарет мечети Хасана Мурада кушбеги не сохранился. В настоящее время сохранился лишь небольшой минарет слева от входной двери в фасадной части.\nВ настоящее время в мечети работает мастерская по резьбе по дереву.\n\n\nМЕЧЕТЬ БАГБАНЛИ\nМечеть Багбанли расположена к юго-востоку от Ичанкала. Эта махаллинская мечеть была построена в 1809 году Пахлавоном Кули и отличается своей красотой.\nНа месте мечети раньше была мечеть Зубайдаханим, которая изначально была построена из сырцового кирпича методом нигирик (чубкори). Вот уже прошло более двухсот лет с момента восстановления мечети, местные жители считают гробницу, пристроенную к ней на западе, «Мавзолеем Малика хоним». Эта могила – могила Зубайдаханима\nСвоим видом эта крупнокупольная мечеть напоминает памятник XIV-XV веков, причина тому, её внутренние орнаменты, резьба двух столбов на крыльце, написанные на них хадисы, характерны для этого периода.\nНадпись на мраморной плите на стене над входом в мечеть сделана на персидском языке на письме насталик, и ее перевод приводится ниже:\nМастер хорошего качества Пахлавонкули,\nОн получил помощь по милости Аллаха.\nЗа верную жену,\nРади Всевышнего.\nОн построил великолепную высокую мечеть,\nОна получила свою красоту и чистоту с рая.\nВышитая, как золотая монета,\nВсе купола и потолки радуют душу.\nОчисти сердечный дворец и религию её,\nОсвободи свое тело из адского огня.\nТысяча двести двадцать четыре,\nЭто чудесная её история.\n\n\nМЕЧЕТЬ ОТАМУРОДА (МАТРИЗО) КУШБЕГИ\nМечеть Отамурода (Матризо) Кушбеги была построена в 1816 году Отамуродом Кушбеги как мечеть махаллив Ичанкала. На мраморном столбе летнего крыльца мечети сохранилась надпись «дата 1232 год хиджры». Минарет мечети не сохранился. Мечеть также имеет многоколонный летний навес и зимнюю мечеть, построенную в форме квадрата.\nМечеть Отамурода Кушбеги имеется алтарь на летнем крыльце со стороны киблы, с правой стороны от алтаря находится кафедра для проповедей и с левой стороны – вход в зимнюю мечеть и специальные места для чтения Корана. Алтарь сделан в форме арки, сталактиты украшены резьбой.\nЛетнее крыльцо мечети примечательно резными колоннами. 6 колонн летнего крыльца состоят из 4 арок и 2 ступеней по строительной технологии и идеально вписаны в архитектурную композицию\nПри строительстве мечети использовались обожженные кирпичи размером 26,0х26,0х4,5 см. На северо-восточной части мечетирасположено помещение для омовения.\n\n\nБЕЛАЯ МЕЧЕТЬ\nВнешний вид мечети, тенистое прохладное крыльцо, окруженное с трех сторон, и три двери однокуполного здания указывают на то, что мечеть является местом собраний. Её древняя часть (фундамент) была построена одновременно с баней Анушахана. Но надписи на резных дверях указывают на то, что здание было построено в 1838-1842 годах. К тому же времени все постройки вокруг площади были в значительной степени застроены, и теперь мастерам пришлось возводить здание на небольшой сохранившейся площади. Архитектура этого здания должна была отражать величие площади, и не должна была отличаться от соседних жилых домов, и хивинские мастера отлично справились с этой задачей\nКупол мечети состоит из комнаты и балкона, в помещении установлены хоры центрального купола (6,35 х 6,35). Помещение было расширено за счет арок. Структура крыльца и боковых стен четко определяет композицию фасада мечети. Высотный купол над плоской крышей в сочетании с квадратным основанием дает вид лестницы. Удачное расположение мечети позволило разместить алтарь на южной стене. Это позволяет одинаково молиться в комнате и на крыльце. Когда мастера строили и украшали мечеть, они строили ее в строгом стиле и ограничивались простыми украшениями. На деревянных столбах резные узоры почти отсутствуют, только верхушки колонны сделаны из гипсов, а мастера искусства резьбы по дереву Одина Каландар угли Нурмухаммад и Саидмухаммад угли Каландар продемонстрировали свое мастерство на декоре трех дверей. Исламские узоры и резбы дверей выдержаны в едином стиле\nВ настоящее время в мечети работает ремесленная мастерская.\n\n\nМЕЧЕТЬ ШЕЙХА КАБИРА\nМечеть шейха Кабира построена на территории кладбище вокруг мавзолея Пахлавона Махмуда, то есть в северной части комплекса. Мечеть шейха Кабира была построена во времена правления Мухаммеда Рахимхана II.\nОбъёмная композиция мечети шейха Кабира ориентирована с севера на юг, а мечеть имеет большую комнату-купол. Планировка мечети проста, с резной деревянной дверью, большим куполом, узоры по углам купола и отдельное крыльцо мечети создают своеобразие. Алтарь и полки на стене крыльца, а также красивые деревянные столбы и стойки придают особый шарм мечети.\nСогласно плану мечети Шейха Кабира, общие размеры составляют 10,20 х 10,0 метра, а высота полки мечети - 4,50 метра. А высота купола мечети 11,55 метра.\nСегодня мечеть шейха Кабира была прекрасно отреставрирована.",
      "JUMA MASJID\nHazoraspdagi Juma masjidi keyingi tadqiqotlarga ko‘ra, O‘rta Osiyodagi eng qadimiy masjidlardan biri hisoblanadi. Xorazm Ma’mun akademiyasi arxeolog olimlari shurf qazib aniqlashlaricha, masjidga X asrda asos solingan.\nHozirda faqat devorlari va bitta yog‘och o‘ymakori eshigi saqlanib qolgan masjid o‘z davrida Xivadagi Juma masjid kabi ko‘p ustunli (5 qator) masjid bo‘lgan. Umumiy hajmi 25x21 m. Hozirda ustun o‘rinlari va ayrim marmar taxtalar saqlanib qolgan. Masjdi devorlariga ravoq shaklida uncha chuqur bo‘lmagan tokchalar ishlangan, boshqa bezak berilmagan. Janubiy devorda mehrob o‘rni saqlanib qolgan. Masjid eshigi yog‘och o‘ymakorligining ajoyib namunalari – islmi naqshlar bilan bezatilgan.Masjid ustun va eshiklari, tom qismlari Sho‘rolar zamonida talon-taroj qilingan. Masjid devorlari ochiq holatda bo‘lgani bois yomg‘ir ta’sirida yoriqlar paydo bo‘lgan, masjidda shoshilinch ravishda ta’mirlash va tiklash ishlarini olib borish zarur. Agar masjid eski usulda yopilsa, bu yerda muzey tashkil qilish va sayyohlikni rivojlantirishda foydalanish mumkin.\n\n\nJUMA MASJID\nMasjid Ollohning uyi, namoz o‘qishga mo‘ljallangan bino. Xivaning Jome’ (Juma) masjidi o‘rta asrlarda shaharning ko‘zga ko‘ringan binolaridan biri bo‘lib, o‘ziga xos qurilishi va hajmi bilan ajralib turgan. Masjid 55x46m maydonni egallab, ko‘p ustunli qilib qurilgan. Bu bino Ichon qal’aning sharqiy va g‘arbiy darvozalarini tutashtiruvchi katta ko‘cha yoqasida joylashgan.\nX asrda Xorazmga kelgan arab sayyohi al-Maqdisiy Xivaning Juma masjidini birinchi marta tilga oladi. Ko‘hna masjid buzilib uning o‘rniga 1788 yili xuddi o‘sha reja asosida ancha kengaytirib hozirgi masjid bino qilingan. Masjid binosining tashqi ko‘rinishi juda sodda, balandligi 4,5 metr, minorasining balandligi esa 42 metrga teng. Masjid darvozasi shimolga qaratib qurilgan bo‘lib, shimoldan esgan shamol masjid o‘rtasida ochilgan ikkita kattagina tuynikdan chiqib ketgan. Tuynik pastida qadimda balxi tutlar o‘sgan, bu shu davrda masjid ichidagi havoni tozalab turishga kattagina yordam bergan, Juma masjid bir qavatli tekis tomli imorat bo‘lib, uning to‘sinli shipini 3,15x3,15 metr tartibda joylashgan 213 ustun ko‘tarib turadi.\nMasjidning mehrobi xonaning janubiy devorida joylashgan. Mehrob, odatdagidek alohida ko‘rinib turishi uchun uning yonlariga baland tokchalar ishlangan bo‘lib, shifti esa balandroq qilib qurilgan. Mehrob qubbasidagi sodda ganchkorlik bezaklar va shu bezak yaqinidagi devorga ishlangan rang-barang ochilgan gulsafsar va na’matakni tasvir etuvchi naqshlar XVIII asr oxiri va XX asrlarda ishlangan. Mehrobning ikki yonidagi devorlariga o‘rnatilgan marmar toshlarga o‘ymakor xatlar bitilgan, xatlarning biri hijriy sana 1203 (1788-89) masjid mulki va mablag‘ hadya etilishi munosabati bilan tuzilgan vaqfnoma bitilgan. Unda aytilishicha, vazir Abdurahmon amri bilan 1203 hijriy yilda Kuyuktom (Go‘ktom- hozirgi Qo‘shko‘pir tumanidagi qishloq) va Bekobod qishloqlarida masjidga vaqf yerlari ajratilganligi va daromadni xayr-ehsonga hamda masjid zaruriyatiga sarf qilish haqidagi ma’lumotlar mavjud. Ikkinchi marmar taxta bir oz kichik bo‘lib, unga 1080 yil hijriy (1666)ni ko‘rsatuvchi tarix yozilgan.\nJanubiy fasaddagi o‘ymakor eshikka bitilgan xatda 1788-89 yillarda Abdurahmon Mehtar ismli shaxs boshchiligida masjid ta’mirlandi deyilgan. Masjid ichkarisida qadimgi naqshinkor ustunlardan 15 tasi saqlanib qolgan. Eng qadimgi ustunlarda ko‘zagi (ustun tagi) shapaloq barglarga ega, tanasining yuqori qismi muntazam raxli, o‘rtasiga esa gir aylantirib xatti kufiy yozuvi yozilgan, shakllar chuqur o‘yib ishlangan. XIV asr ustunlarida esa naqshlar ko‘p bo‘lib, yozuvlar xatti nasxda berilgan. \nBu nodir yodgorlik 1979-1983 va 1996-1997 yillarda qayta ta’mirlangan. Hozirda me’moriy ob’yekt sifatida sayyohlarga xizmat qilmoqda.\n\n\nYoRMUHAMMAD DEVON (SAYYID OTA) MASJIDI\nYormuhammad Devon masjidi Sayyid ota masjidi nomi bilan ham yuritiladi, buning sababi masjid Sayyid A’lovuddin maqbarasi yonida joylashganligidan, shu ulug‘ insonning xotirasi uchun nomlangan. Masjid Sharqiy tomondan Abdurasulboy madrasasi bilan tutashgan.\nMunis va Ogahiyning “Firdavs ul iqbol” asarida Yor Muhammad devonbegining faoliyati haqida ko‘p ma’lumotlar keltirilib, jumladan shunday deyiladi “mahrami asrori sohibqironiy (xonning o‘z sir-asrorlariga sherik qiladigan eng yaqin kishisi) Yormuhammad devonbegi”. Devonbegi sayyidlar xonadonidan bo‘lgan va bu haqda masjidning mehrobi ustida saqlanib qolgan yozuvlar ma’lumot beradi: “Masjidki binokard hamon baxsh valiyat avlodi Muhammad...”.\nMasjid o‘sha davrda kichikroq mahallaga mo‘ljallab qurilgan bo‘lib, uzoq yillar davomida bu masjidda mahallada yashovchi fuqarolar juma namozlarini ado etib kelganlar.\n\n\nTOSHMASJID\nToshmasjid XVIII asr oxirida qurilgan mahalla masjididir. Bino shu qurilgan davr me’morchiligi an’analarida barpo qilingan. Toshmasjidni o‘rgangan arxeologlar uning o‘rnida u qurilgunga qadar ham aholining ommaviy tadbirlar o‘tkazadigan joyi bo‘lganligini aniqlashdi. Haqiqatdan ham hozirgi kungacha Toshmasjidda ommaviy udumlar va tadbirlar o‘tkazilib kelinmoqda.\nBino davr o‘tishi bilan turli maqsadlarda foydala-nish uchun qayta jihozlangan va ta’mirlangan. 1997 yili Xivaning 2500 yilligi yubileyi munosabati bilan bino ilmiy asosda ishlangan loyiha asosida tubdan mukammal ta’mir-lanib, asl holiga keltirildi.\nBinodan oqilona foydalanish maqsadini ko‘zlagan holda uni mahalla fuqarolar faollarini iltimosi va tashabbussini e’tiborga olib, Soyot mahallasiga saqlash asosida berildi.\n\n\nHASAN MUROD QUSHBEGI MASJIDI\nHasan Murod qushbegi masjidi XVIII asr oxiri XIX boshlarida Bog‘cha darvoza yaqinida qurilgan. Mazkur masjid aka-ukalar Xasan Murod qushbegi va birgalikda Niyoz otaliq tomonidan mahalla ichida bunyod qilingan.\nMasjidda bir ustunli yozgi ayvon va gumbaz bilan bostirilgan qishqi masjid bor. Masjid turar joy imoratlaridan uncha tafovut etmaydi. Eshiklari islimiy naqshlar bilan bezatilgan.\nHasan Murod qushbegi masjidining asosiy minorasi saqlanmagan. Hozirda fakat fasad kismidagi kirish eshigining chap tomonida joylashgan kichik xajmdagi minora saklanib qolgan.\nHozirda masjidda yog‘och o‘ymakorligi ustaxonasi joylashgan.\n\n\nBOGʻBONLI MASJIDI\nBog‘bonli masjidi Ichon qal’aning janubi-sharqida joylashgan. Bu mahalla masjidi 1809 yilda Pahlavon Quli tomonidan qurilgan bo‘lib, o‘zining ko‘rkamligi bilan ajralib turadi.\nMasjid o‘rnida avval xom g‘ishtli nigirik (cho‘bkori) usulida qurilgan Zubaydaxonim masjidi bo‘lgan ekan. Masjidning qayta qurilganiga ikki yuz yildan oshdi-ki, mahalliy aholi unga g‘arbiy tomondan yopishtirib qurilgan mozorni “Malika xonim mozori” deb hisoblaydilar. Bu qabr Zubaydaxonimning qabridir.\nKatta bir gumbazli bu masjid ko‘rinishdan XIV-XV asrlar yodgorligini eslatadi, bunga sabab uning ichki bezaklari, ayvonidagi ikkita ustunining o‘yma naqshlari, ularga yozilgan hadislar shu davrga xosligidir.\nMasjid kirish eshigining tepasidagi devorga o‘rnatilgan marmar taxtachadagi yozuv, fors tili, nasta’liq xatida bo‘lib, uning tarjimasi quyidagcha:\nYaxshi xislatli usta Pahlavonquli,\nAllohning lutfidan madad oldi.\nO‘zining jufti haloli uchun,\nQudrat egasining (Alloh) rizosiga.\nBir ajoyib oliy masjid bino qildi,\nU o‘z chiroy va tozaligini jannatdan oldi.\nXuddi ziynatlangan tilla tangadek naqshlanib,\nBarcha qubba va shiftlari dilni quvontiradi.\nUning dil qasri va dinini obod qil,\nHam do‘zax o‘tidan tanini ozod qil.\nBir ming ikki yuz yigirma to‘rt edi, \nUning ajoyib tarixi ey hushyor.\n\n\nOTAMUROD (MATRIZO) QUSHBEGI MASJIDI\nOtamurod (Matrizo) qushbegi masjidi 1816 yilda Otamurod qushbegi tomonidan mahalla masjidi sifatida Ichon qal’ada barpo etilgan. Masjidning yozgi ayvonidagi marmar ustunda hijriy 1232 sanasi saqlangan. Masjid minorasi saqlanmagan. Masjidda ko‘p ustunli yozgi ayvon va kvadrat shaklida qurilgan qishki masjid ham bor.\nOtamurod qushbegi masjidi yozgi ayvonining to‘rida, qibla tomonida mehrob joylashgan, mehrobning o‘ng tomonida va’zxonlik uchun minbar, chap tomonida esa qishki masjidga kirish eshigi va qur’on o‘kiladigan maxsus joylar ajratilgan. Mehrob arkasimon qilib, stalaktidalari ganch bilan bezatilgan.\nMasjidning yozgi ayvoni o‘ymakor ustunlari bilan diqqatga sazovordir. Yozgi ayvonning 6 ta ustuni qurilish texnikasi bo‘yicha 4 ta ravoqdan va 2 ta qadamdan iborat qilib, juda mukammal holda me’moriy kompozisiyaga xos ravishda ishlangan.\nMasjid qurilishida hajmi 26,0x 26,0x4,5sm bo‘lgan pishgan g‘ishtdan foydalanilgan. Masjidning shimoli– sharqiy qismida tahoratxona joylashgan.\n\n\nOQMASJID\nMasjidning tashqi ko‘rinishi, uch tarafdan o‘rab olingan soya-salqin ayvoni, bir gumbazli binosining uchta eshigi masjidning jamoat yig‘ilish joyi ekanligidan darak beradi. Uning qadimgi qismi (poydevori) Anushaxon hammomi bilan bir vaqtda qurilgan. Lekin o‘ymakor eshiklardagi yozuvlar binoning 1838-1842 yillarda qurilganini ko‘rsatadi. Xuddi shu vaqtga kelib maydon atrofidagi hamma binolar asosan qurilgan bo‘lib, endi ustalar qolgan kichik bir sahnda bino qurishlari kerak edi. Bu binoni me’morchiligi maydonning mahobatini ifoda etishi, qo‘shni uy-joy imoratlaridan uncha tafovut etmaydigan bo‘lishi lozim edi, xivalik ustalar bu vazifani a’lo darjada ado etganlar.\nMasjid gumbazi xona va ayvondan iborat, markaziy gumbaz chorsi (6,35 x 6,35) xonaga o‘rnatilgan. Xona ravoqlar yordamida kengaytirilgan. Ayvon tuzilishi va yon devorlar masjidning fasad kompozisiyasini aniq belgilab turadi. Yassi tom ustidan baland ko‘tarilgan gumbaz kvadrat asosi bilan birgalikda uzoqdan zinapoyasimon ko‘rinish baxsh etadi. Masjidning qulay joylashganligi mehrobni janubiy devorga joylashtirish imkonini bergan. Bu esa xonada va ayvonda baravar namoz o‘qish imkonini beradi. Ustalar masjidni qurganlarida va bezak berganlarida sodda uslubda qurib, sodda bezaklar berish bilan cheklanganlar. Yog‘och ustunlarda o‘yma naqshlar deyarli yo‘q, faqat ustun tepasi xakamkoriy-pilaklardan terib yasalgan, yog‘och o‘ymakorligi san’atini ustalaridan Odina Qalandar o‘g‘li Nurmuhammad va Sayidmuhammad o‘g‘li Qalandarlar uchta eshik bezagida o‘z mahoratlarini namoyish etganlar. Eshiklarning islimiy naqshlari va jimjimasi bir xil uslubda ishlangan.\nHozirda masjidda hunarmandchilik ustaxonasi faoliyat yuritmoqda.\n\n\nSHAYX KABIR MASJIDI\nShayx Kabir masjidi – Pahlavon Mahmud maqbarasining atrofidagi qabriston hududida, ya’ni majmuaning shimoliy kismida qurilgan. Shayx Kabir masjidi Muhammad Raximxon II hukmronligi davrida bunyod etilgan\nShayx Kabir masjidining hajmiy kompozisiyasi shimol – janub yo‘nalishida bo‘lib, masjidda katta bir xonako – gumbaz joylashgan. Masjid rejasi oddiy bo‘lib, yog‘och o‘ymakori eshik, katta gumbazi, gumbazning burchaklaridagi muqarnaslari va alohida qurilgan masjid ayvoni o‘ziga xoslik kasb etadi. Ayvonning kibla devoriga ishlangan mehrob va tokchalari hamda ayvonga o‘rnatilgan chiroyli yog‘och ustun va xarilari masjidga alohida ko‘rk bag‘ishlaydi.\nShayx Kabir masjidining rejasi bo‘yicha umumiy o‘lchami – 10,20 x 10,0 metr bo‘lib, masjid peshtoqining balandligi - 4,50 metrni tashkil qiladi. Masjid gumbazining balandligi esa – 11,55 metr.\nHozirda Shayx Kabir masjidi juda chiroyli qilib ta’mirlangan"
    ),
